    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_9",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a collector-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) in Carbon Black. This specimen is powered by the S54 3.2L inline-six, featuring six individual throttle bodies and a high-pressure double VANOS system, delivering linear power up to its 8000 RPM redline. The drivetrain is anchored by a Getrag 420G six-speed manual transmission and a limited-slip M-differential. Mechanical integrity is paramount: the rod bearings and VANOS hub have been serviced, and the rear subframe has been proactively reinforced to ensure structural longevity. The suspension utilizes refreshed bushings and original-specification dampers to maintain the chassis's renowned balance. With zero paint imperfections and a pristine interior, this vehicle represents a mechanically optimized example of naturally aspirated M-power engineering.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 11
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
