    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offered is an exceptional 1994 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S), a pinnacle of lightweight engineering and rotary performance. This example retains its numbers-matching 13B-REW power plant, featuring a perfectly synchronized sequential twin-turbocharger system and documented high-compression rotors. The chassis maintains its legendary 50/50 weight distribution, paired with a pristine double-wishbone suspension and a factory Torsen limited-slip differential. The exterior retains its original high-gloss finish with zero evidence of oxidation, while the interior plastics show no signs of the typical heat-cycling fatigue. Mechanically sorted with a refreshed vacuum system and OEM cooling components, this vehicle represents a turn-key, investment-grade specimen of the golden era of JDM sports cars.",
